Uâ€‹gh. Sorry! This Project seemed like such a great idea, and perfect for me right now to get started on a blog in between classes. Two hours and I'd have my WordPress up and running and ready to go! Did it seem too good to be true? No because in my experience Coursera DOES DELIVER!! But not this time. I have wasted my entire day trying to get on with this project. First Tech issues -- but they are forgivable. And the Support at Coursera are also very good so I spoke with them about it. Tried a different browser. Stil no joy but ok -- I found away around it and persevered. Next, the instructor's screen is completely and consistently out of synch with the USER screen -- which meant only one thing for me -- that the course was designed and delivered a while back and Word Press have changed their layouts, and navigations..... so that made following tricky. Third, the screens are WAY TOO SMALL and actually not at all clear so it was difficult enough to follow but visibility was quite POOR trying to keep both screens open on the page. I decided that I have enough no how to go onto wordpress and try to pick up where I left off.... And WordPress had not got my details saved from what I"d set up on the project. That confused me!! No progress made at all today. Back to square one -- quite frustrated. That did not work at all for me.  Disheartened by this offer. Thanks for the idea, but please update and upgrade this offer or take it off the menu.
